grph.in_memory

Class InMemoryGrph

  • java.lang.Object
    • grph.Grph
      • grph.in_memory.InMemoryGrph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DirectedGraph, DirectedHyperGraph, DirectedSimpleGraph, EdgeSet, GrphPrimitives, UndirectedGraph, UndirectedHyperGraph, UndirectedSimpleGraph, UnqualifiedGraph, VertexSet, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EuclideanGrph

    public class InMemoryGrph
extends Grph
implements java.io.Serializable
    The basic data-structure. It mainly defines and implements the data structure required for vertex/edge incidence. The methods in this API are written using two rules: 1. they are non-permissive: for example deleting an element that is not in the graph will cause an error 2. elements are created on-the-fly, when possible.
    See Also:
